-- Tottenham Wants to Get Striker Zarate on Loan, Mirror Says: Soccer Roundup
-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 2012-01-24T12:03:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-24/tottenham-wants-to-get-striker-zarate-on-loan-mirror-says-soccer-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable links to the Web.  Spurs Loan  Tottenham coach  Harry Redknapp  wants to sign Lazio striker
Mauro Zarate on loan, the  Daily Mirror  reported.  The Argentine forward, who played for Birmingham during the
2007-8 season, is on loan at Inter Milan, the Mirror said.  Real’s Granero  Liverpool is in talks about signing Real Madrid’s Esteban
Granero on loan, the  Daily Mirror  reported.  The attacking midfielder has played four times for the
Spanish club this season, the Mirror said.  Leiva Return  Liverpool’s  Lucas Leiva  has returned to the club for
rehabilitation from a season-ending knee injury, the  Daily
Express  reported.  Leiva spent the last six weeks in his native  Brazil , where
he had surgery, the Express said.  Lampard Out  Frank Lampard  will miss Chelsea’s FA Cup fourth-round game
at Queens Park Rangers on Jan. 28 because of injury,  the Sun 
reported.  The midfielder suffered a calf injury during last weekend’s
goalless draw against Norwich, the Sun said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
